    "As an indicative example, when Narendra et al compared a number of (highly reputable) DREAM challenges winning algorithms for pathway reverse engineering and contrasted them with additional algorithms with fresh datasets, very hard gold standards, and using a variety of loss functions, the previous winners did not exhibit superior performances and in some cases were substantially underperforming especially with respect to several loss functions not originally examined [21].",
    "It is also common to see discussions of how the sample size may affect ability to learn specific classes of target functions [55,56].What is omitted from most technical and lay public discourse alike, however, are the effects of data design (Chapter \"Data Design\") and model selection and error estimation (Chapters \"Principles of Rigorous Development and of Appraisal of ML and AI Methods and Systems\", \"The Development Process and Lifecycle of Clinical Grade and Other Safety and Performance-sensitive AI/ML Models\", \"Overfitting, Underfitting and General Model Overconfidence and Underperformance Pitfalls and Best Practices in Machine Learning and AI\")."
